The paper deals with compressed sensing over arbitrarily connected networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The focus on inter-signal correlation and distributed algorithms suggests signal processing (cs.SI) and distributed systems (cs.DS) as likely categories. Finally, the use of simulations to demonstrate performance suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as a possible category as well.
